<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Import Catalyst Center Services in ITSI on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/scenarios/network-event-intelligence/2-import-catalyst-center-services-in-itsi/</link><description>Recent content in Import Catalyst Center Services in ITSI on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/scenarios/network-event-intelligence/2-import-catalyst-center-services-in-itsi/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Install the Cisco Enterprise Networks Content Pack</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/scenarios/network-event-intelligence/2-import-catalyst-center-services-in-itsi/1-cisco-enterprise-networks-content-pack/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/scenarios/network-event-intelligence/2-import-catalyst-center-services-in-itsi/1-cisco-enterprise-networks-content-pack/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In this section you will install the Cisco Enterprise Networks Content Pack which provides pre-built services, KPIs, and data integrations for Cisco network infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise: Install the Cisco Enterprise Networks Content Pack&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.&lt;/strong&gt; In ITSI Navigate to &lt;strong&gt;Configuration -&amp;gt; Data Integrations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2.&lt;/strong&gt; Select &lt;strong&gt;Content Library&lt;/strong&gt; in the tabs under Data Integrations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12" y2="12"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12.01" y2="8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Info&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>ITSI Service and KPI Validation</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/scenarios/network-event-intelligence/2-import-catalyst-center-services-in-itsi/2-itsi-service-kpi-import-and-setup/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/scenarios/network-event-intelligence/2-import-catalyst-center-services-in-itsi/2-itsi-service-kpi-import-and-setup/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;With ITSI 4.21 manual import processes are replaced by a guided workflow and pre-built data integrations. The content pack includes service import modules that discover and build the service hierarchy for Meraki and Catalyst Center automatically.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise: Import Services and Configure Alerts&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M9 18h6M10 22h4M12 2a7 7 0 0 0-4 12.7V17h8v-2.3A7 7 0 0 0 12 2z"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Tip&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Validate the Configuration</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/scenarios/network-event-intelligence/2-import-catalyst-center-services-in-itsi/3-itsi-validate-configuration/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/scenarios/network-event-intelligence/2-import-catalyst-center-services-in-itsi/3-itsi-validate-configuration/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Confirm that the imported services and KPIs are calculating correctly, and that the alert pipeline from Catalyst Center is active before moving on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Exercise: Validate the Configuration&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.&lt;/strong&gt; Navigate to the &lt;strong&gt;Service Analyzer&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;gt; &lt;strong&gt;Default Service Analyzer&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should see the services you imported and the KPIs that are part of the Catalyst Center Site Service Template.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It may take a few minutes for your services and KPIs to show a health status.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>